    "The Bayesian classifier uses the Bayes rule to calculate the posterior probability for each class c i.",
    "NB is based on the simplifying assumption that the features, y, are independent of the class.",
    "Therefore, the probability can be calculated by using the conditional probabilities of each feature given in the class.",
    "So, the posterior probability, P (C i |y), is expressed as in Eqs.",
    "(1) and (2)."
  ],
